    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>I am favored with y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letter of June 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; admire your kindness to <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>. He may command all I can
                    do for him. I shall soon set out on a little ramble. which will take till the
                    middle of August when I hope to hear from you again. Please to forward the
                    inclosed first perusing that to <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Low</persName>. The Box I dare say will be safely arrived by my return.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> July 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                    1775.</dateline></closer>

            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p><persName ref="pe0015"><hi rend="superscript">Free</hi>RMostyn</persName></p>
                <p><stamp type="frank">FREE</stamp></p>
                <p><stamp type="handstamp">NORTHOP</stamp></p>
                <p><stamp type="postmark">5<lb/>IY</stamp></p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
